content: Interesting idea, long way to go. I have to be completely honest, I don't quite understand why people find this so accurate. I feel that anyone from the "outside" would find this app gaudy and ridiculous. Which is not fair to psychedelic experience, which is everything but that. Technology is nowhere near good enough to even begin making decent replications. But certainly better than what's out there. Good work. Keep it up.
replyContent: Thank you for the review. I think its pretty clear to anyone who has had psychedelic experiences, that no human or machine will ever be able to replicate completely subjective human experiences fully, especially people who decide to buy this. I would never open the app with expectation that it will be like the real thing.

content: The visuals are pretty realistic, but some app features don't currently work. Like the gallery and take pictures button don't do anything, but I'm willing to chalk that up to this app being very new. VR support would also be an interesting feature to be added in later.
replyContent: This is weird, I have exactly the same phone as you and have no issues running it. Can you recheck the apps Permissions, specifically storage. Some phones kinda ignore storage permissions and they need to be enabled separately. We are already working on a fix for this since its pretty random and not consistent accross devices
